title: PPPP Candidate Sarfraz Ahmed Bugti wins PB-10 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan Peopleâ€™s Party Parliamentarians candidate Sarfraz Ahmed Bugti has won the Balochistan Assembly election from PB-10, Dera Bugti by securing 52,485 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Jamori Watan Party candidate Gehram Bugti who bagged 25,773 votes.
Overall voters turnout remained 60.45 percent.
